                <p>$GLOBALS is a superglobal variable, which is also an array that stores all the global scope variables and is used to access global variables from anywhere in the PHP program.</p>
                <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>
                <pre class="bg-black text-white p-2"><code>&lt;?php
$x = 10;
$y = 11;

function add() {
    $GLOBALS['z'] = $GLOBALS['x'] + $GLOBALS['y'];
}

add();
echo $z;
?&gt;</code></pre>
